{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe single `state[\"signature\"]` slot is last-writer-wins, so one kind clobbers another.\nThis is the root-cause fix and the riskiest slice (back-compat + compaction), done first.\nIt is ADDITIVE and behavior-preserving: it introduces the `attestations` map without\nchanging any existing signature/mirror semantics, so it is safe to ship before the gate\nmigration (929e).\n## What\nAdd `state[\"attestations\"]`, a kind-keyed map (per-key LWW, like `process_workflow_run`).\n`process_signature`:\n- MIRROR (unchanged semantics): `state[\"signature\"] = record` for EVERY SIGNATURE event,\n  EXACTLY as today — including a blank/retired event (manifest=[], retired=True), which\n  still clears the mirror. This preserves 100% of current behavior for the four existing\n  `state.get(\"signature\")` consumers and for `retire_attested_pin` (which stays in this\n  slice; it is removed only in 929e, together with the reopen-aware validity that replaces\n  it — so there is NO window where reopen-invalidation is missing).\n- MAP (new, additive): if the event is kindable (non-empty manifest with a derivable kind),\n  also set `attestations[kind] = record`. Kind = SIGNED `manifest[0]` substring before the\n  first \":\" (authoritative); `data[\"kind\"]` is used only as a hint iff it matches, else\n  ignored. A blank/retired/unkindable event is SKIPPED for the map (it stays out of the\n  map; it does not and cannot clear a kind). Nothing in this slice READS the map yet, so the\n  map's presence is inert until cc1b/929e wire consumers to it.\nAlso add `state[\"last_reopened_at\"]` (in `process_status`): the timestamp of the most recent\n`closed -> open` transition (pre-update status == \"closed\" and target == \"open\"); null if\nnever. (Consumed by compute_validity in 929e; recorded here so the data exists.)\nRead fold-in: an OLD SNAPSHOT whose compiled_state carries only `signature` (no\n`attestations`) is folded into the map on restore, under the kind derived from that\nrecord's own `manifest[0]` (dropped if blank/unkindable). New SNAPSHOTs carry BOTH\n`attestations` and the `signature` mirror automatically (the reducer maintains both).\n`_present.py` `public_state()`: add a DEDICATED `attestations` branch stripping the\n`signature` (HMAC hex) subkey from each per-kind record (the flat `_INTERNAL_SUBKEYS`\ncannot express a wildcard kind level); retain the legacy single-`signature` strip.\n114f owns the canonical per-record shape.\n## Scope\n`src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py` (`process_signature`, `process_status`,\n`process_snapshot`), `src/rebar/reducer/_present.py`, `src/rebar/reducer/_state.py`,\n`ticket_state.schema.json`. No change to the signed payload; no change to retirement /\nmirror semantics; `retire_attested_pin` untouched here.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `attestations` map added; `process_signature` sets the mirror for EVERY event (old semantics preserved, incl. blank/retired clearing the mirror) AND additively sets `attestations[kind]` only for kindable events.\n- [ ] Kind from authoritative `manifest[0]`; `data[\"kind\"]` only a validated hint; blank/unkindable events skipped for the map (never clobber a kind).\n- [ ] `state[\"last_reopened_at\"]` records the most recent closed->open timestamp (null if never).\n- [ ] Old-snapshot fold-in files the legacy record under its manifest-derived kind (dropped if blank/unkindable); new SNAPSHOTs carry both map and mirror.\n- [ ] `public_state()` dedicated `attestations` branch strips HMAC hex from every per-kind record; legacy strip retained; no hex in show/MCP.\n- [ ] Compaction/SNAPSHOT round-trips all kinds; empty `attestations` omitted; `retire_attested_pin`/mirror semantics unchanged in this slice."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782795329388468001,"uuid":"4ed062d8-f89a-4658-9929-985b6fb86ab8"}